Description: -Heavy duty rock/gig back included. (Missing one tone control knob piece but still works perfectly) In terms of playability, Eastwood’s Airline delivered across the board. The Gibson-style Tune-O-Matic bridge and tuning pegs keep the guitar in tune even after vigorous playing. The neck feels solid and smooth and the guitar handles well and is comfortable to hold. As for tone shaping, there are two Alnico Hot-10 Humbucker pickups, each with volume and tone controls. The guitar also features a three-way pick-up selector switch and a master volume control; All in all, the Eastwood Airline 2P DLX boasts a vintage design, superior sound, and effortless playability. It is a well-made guitar that is both much cheaper and much easier to locate than the original. If you are in the market for a new guitar and are intrigued by the odd designs and affordable price of an Eastwood, go ahead and take the plunge. You won’t be disappointed.
